    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on several favorable matchups today, with **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) leading the way as our elite offensive engines. **Kyle Tucker** benefits immensely from an excellent park factor and a soft matchup against Quintana, while **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start despite a modest penalty for facing a pitcher adept at holding runners; his leadoff position and favorable wind conditions keep his floor exceptionally high. **Andy Pages** (75.63) also presents significant value, as his strong platoon profile and the favorable park environment against Quintana have pushed him into the high-70s, making him a primary source of run production.\n\nTactically, the lineup is heavily leaning into the favorable matchup against Elder, elevating **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), **Drake Baldwin** (72.11), and **Brady House** (61.32) into our primary active roster. The most difficult decision rested on the bench, where **Nolan Schanuel** (50.08) just barely missed the cut. While **Nolan Schanuel** provides solid contact, the optimizer preferred the high-upside ceiling of **Dominic Smith** (59.79), whose platoon advantage against Irvin created a safer path to points in a 5x5 format that prioritizes efficiency. \n\nWe are monitoring the status of several players, specifically **Jacob Wilson**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, who are currently listed with pending lineups. **Jacob Wilson** faces a slight downgrade due to the park factor and the presence of Hancock on the mound, and we are proceeding with caution regarding **Josh Lowe**, whose matchup against the elite Dylan Cease suppresses his base projection despite his potential for stolen bases. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** remains a marginal play today; facing Detmers is an uphill battle, but his raw talent keeps him relevant in the utility slot over the bench options. We continue to hold **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill** in reserve, while **Jordan Westburg** remains on the IL, as we look to maximize our limited daily game caps.",
